	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">De conveniendo quod scribis<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2"><persName type="citizen_name" ref="p495" cert="high">Bullingers</persName> Brief ist nicht erhalten.</note>, placet.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vide modo, ut animum aequiorem adferas in <persName ref="p467" cert="high">Bucerum</persName> et suspicionem minus tecum adportes, quae valde rebus his obstant.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Verum de animo tuo candidissimo nil dubito, mi <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p495" cert="high">Bullingere</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Proinde, sicubi convenire vis, adero magno studio.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Utinam <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l41" cert="high">Bernatibus</placeName> esset concordię studium amplius!</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quid opus adeo est sine nobis de concordia statuere atque tumultuari, quasi decedere nos a<pb type="edition" next="62"/> confessione recepta velimus<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Vermutlich bezieht sich Grynäus auf den Widerstand <placeName type="citizen_name" ref="l41" cert="high">Berns</placeName> gegen eine Anerkennung der Confessio Tetrapolitana; vgl. <bibl>HBBW</bibl> VI <ref target="file10856">[Nr. 817]</ref>, S. 282, Anm. 5.</note>?</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Sed frustra iam hęc.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Da operam, ut vere in domino coalescamus animis, quae difficultas summa semper fuit ac, nisi fallor, futura est semper.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Haud multum nobis res discrepat, si non sit aliquid in animis semper infestum.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Oremus itaque vere patrem in coelis, ut copulare nos velit toto pectore et disiecta membra<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Vgl. Horaz, Sermones, 1, 4, 62.</note> pugnantiaque componere.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">O domine</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Christe, da nobis illud cor unum iam aliquando, saltem tuis filiis, ne perpetuo inter hostes nostros evangelii nomen per nos male audiat.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Amen.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="15" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tuus frater in Christo <persName type="citizen_name" ref="p1365" cert="high">Gryneus</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="16" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Saluta <persName ref="p8171" cert="high">Theodorum</persName><note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5"><persName ref="p8171" cert="high">Theodor Bibliander</persName>.</note>, fratres omnes.</s>
					<s n="17" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Valete in domino omnes.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse darunter:]</note>
					<s n="18" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><persName type="citizen_name" ref="p495" cert="high">Bullingero</persName>, fratri charissimo suo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
